        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 9 at 5:47PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 547 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles north of Claude, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Claude.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
